# Dataset Delete

Delete a dataset object. If digests are provided, only those versions are deleted. Otherwise, all versions are deleted.

DELETE

/

v2

/

{entity}

/

{project}

/

datasets

/

{object_id}

Dataset Delete
    
    
    curl --request DELETE \
      --url https://api.example.com/v2/{entity}/{project}/datasets/{object_id} \
      --header 'Authorization: Basic <encoded-value>'
    
    
    {
      "num_deleted": 123
    }

#### Authorizations

HTTPBasicHTTPBearerHTTPBasicHTTPBearer

​

Authorization

string

header

required

Basic authentication header of the form `Basic <encoded-value>`, where `<encoded-value>` is the base64-encoded string `username:password`.

#### Path Parameters

​

entity

string

required

​

project

string

required

​

object_id

string

required

#### Query Parameters

​

digests

string[] | null

List of digests to delete. If not provided, all digests for the dataset will be deleted.

#### Response

Successful Response

​

num_deleted

integer

required

Number of dataset versions deleted

